## Dimension: Dissent Preservation

**Definition**: The degree to which conflicting viewpoints, disagreements, and minority positions are explicitly represented rather than collapsed or suppressed.

**Why This Matters**: UK scientific advice must preserve independence and avoid groupthink. Minority views often flag important uncertainties or risks. Collapsing dissent undermines the integrity of the advice artefact.

